data.meta_description: Lysander Woodward was the son of Asahel Woodward and Harriet House. The family moved to Michigan in 1838, after having lived in Monroe Co., New York for 13 years.  Lysander's interests were varied. He operated a farm of 427 acres. In addition, he was a member of the Rochester band for ten years, in which he played the...
